50|$|During {{the late}} 50's and early 60's, {{she was well}} known as a {{navigator}} for Pat Moss, the sister of Sir Stirling Moss. Their partnership ensured them to compete {{at the same level}} as the men. In 1962, she ended her rally career in order to start a family, marrying the gentleman rally driver, Peter <b>Riley.</b> <b>Pat</b> bounced back, hiring erstwhile driver Pauline Mayman to navigate.|$|R
